    <section id="fs-id1932567" type="problems-exercises" class="problems-exercises"><title>Problems &amp; Exercises</title><exercise id="fs-id1411839" type="problems-exercises">
      <problem id="fs-id3123812">
      <para id="import-auto-id2957114">At what net rate does heat radiate from a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>275</m:mtext><m:msup><m:mtext>-m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> black roof on a night when the roof’s temperature is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>30.</m:mtext><m:mn>0º</m:mn><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> and the surrounding temperature is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>15.</m:mtext><m:mn>0º</m:mn><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>? The emissivity of the roof is 0.900.</para></problem>
        <solution id="fs-id1195513" type="problem-exercises"><para id="fs-id3011992"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mtext>21</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mi/><m:mtext> kW</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math><newline/>
Note that the negative answer implies heat loss to the surroundings.</para></solution>
